node.text:
If you haven’t seen my last post👁
I made some new Rainbow glass cane🌈🌈🌈
I’m going to use it to create a lot of jewelry, pendants, rings and more...it’s great to add as a dot accent on any variety of pieces as well, including straws and pendants
Most of these colors are layered, for example the green is layered with a transparent purple and the purple color is a mixture of two purples that I hand mixed👩🏻‍🏭Before applying. I created a new rod of purple and several new rods of mixed colors just to make it. Even the white isn’t just white☁️, 🌬it’s 3 different whites with an Aqua glow in the dark river running on either side that glows bright blue in the dark🏞🌊
The pendant loop glows bright blue under the blacklight💧☂️
It’s one of my favorite glass colors, a crisp, clear and bright transparent blue that’s too gorgeous to not see in person. 🔱🌈So much work went into just mixing these colors individually and then layering the colors side by side to eventually make 3 separate rods about 2 ft. long each. 
This is a design of cane I’ve done once before but changed a bit for fun this time around. Just literally two tweaks to the OG formula💯. Now is a great time to put in your custom orders if you’d like me to make you a piece of jewelry, a sculpture, straw or any other piece of art with this glass either as the main body or accents. This pendant is for sale🍎🍊🍋🍏💧🍆🍇🌈🌈🌈My next post will be blacklight & glow in the dark pics of it. It is part of my Perspective Capsule series. All it takes sometimes is a shift of perspective to see the beauty all around us and in our situations. It’s a reminder that we all can change our perspective any time we remember we have the choice. It is also very inspired by different significant times in my life that I’ll share with you soon🌟💫

I would HIGHLY recommend it to anyone craving new content from that universe, especially those who love dragons and their lore.

The first Targaryen to set foot on Westeros was Aegon the Conquerer. He rode a massive dragon named Belerion the Black Dread, which was his companion and the key to all his victories.

My reading this week on Belerion, has been reminding me of this available Onyx pendant.
